-- Manchester Utd. Beats Villa 4-0, Leads League by Five Points
-- B y   J a m e s   C o n e
-- 2012-04-15T16:55:52Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-04-15/manchester-utd-beats-villa-4-0-leads-league-by-five-points.html
Manchester United  beat Aston Villa
4-0 to record a seventh straight home win in English soccer’s
Premier League and maintain a five-point lead over Manchester
City through the weekend’s matches.  Wayne Rooney got two goals, while  Danny Welbeck  and Nani
also scored today at Old Trafford as the defending champion
rebounded from a defeat at Wigan in its last match.  United, aiming for a record-extending 20th championship,
tops the standings with 82 points, City has 77, with Arsenal on
64. Tottenham and Newcastle have 59 points, with Spurs ahead on
goal difference, and Chelsea has 57.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Cone at 
 jcone@bloomberg.net  